---
description: How the poller handles failures
globs: "app/poller.py,app/open_meteo.py"
---

The poller must never raise out of its main loop. On any upstream failure:

- Log at WARNING level with structured fields: `city`, `http_status` if available, `attempt`,
  `next_retry_seconds`, and `trace_id`.
- Retry with exponential backoff up to `max_retries` from `app/config.py`.
- After exhausting retries, log at ERROR, skip this city for this cycle, and continue with the
  other cities.
- Never partial-write a reading. If parsing fails halfway through, no database write should happen.

Generated code that uses bare `try: ... except:` or re-raises out of `run_poller()` is incorrect.
